- **`pid_t pid = fork();`**: This line forks the current process into a parent and a child. The return value of `fork()` is used to differentiate between the parent and child processes.
- **`if (pid == -1)`**: Checks if `fork()` failed.
- **`else if (pid == 0)`**: This block runs in the child process. The child prints its PID and then breaks out of the loop to prevent further forking.
- **`else`**: This block runs in the parent process. The parent also prints its PID and can optionally break out of the loop depending on your requirements.

